 and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."],"variants":[{"name":"Isabell","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isabelle","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , now in frequent use in the English-speaking world."]},{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]},{"name":"Isobelle","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabel Ellmden was born about 1395, in Embleton, Durham, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Thomas Langton. She died about 1476, at the age of 83."},"et":{"about 1395–about 1476":"umbes 1395–umbes 1476","1380–1440":"1380–1440","1415–Female":"1415–Surnud","1395–1476":"1395–1476","1415":"1415","about 1415":"umbes 1415","1476":"1476","before 1440":"enne 1440","1440":"1440","1395":"1395","about 1476":"umbes 1476","1380":"1380","about 1395":"umbes 1395","Of, Wynyard, Durham, England":"Wynyard, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Embleton, Durham":"Embleton, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1395–about 1476":"noin 1395–noin 1476","1380–1440":"1380–1440","1415–Female":"1415–Kuollut","1395–1476":"1395–1476","1415":"1415","about 1415":"noin 1415","1476":"1476","before 1440":"ennen vuotta 1440","1440":"1440","1395":"1395","about 1476":"noin 1476","1380":"1380","about 1395":"noin 1395","Of, Wynyard, Durham, England":"Wynyard, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Embleton, Durham":"Embleton, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1395–about 1476":"environ 1395–environ 1476","1380–1440":"1380–1440","1415–Female":"1415–Décédée","1395–1476":"1395–1476","1415":"1415","about 1415":"environ 1415","1476":"1476","before 1440":"avant 1440","1440":"1440","1395":"1395","about 1476":"environ 1476","1380":"1380","about 1395":"environ 1395","Of, Wynyard, Durham, England":"Wynyard, Durham, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Embleton, Durham":"Embleton, Durham, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Isabel Ellmden est née environ 1395, à Embleton, Durham, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Thomas Langton. Elle est décédée environ 1476, à l’âge de 83 ans."},"de":{"about 1395–about 1476":"um 1395–um 1476","1380–1440":"1380–1440","1415–Female":"1415–Verstorben","1395–1476"